Reasoning: The paper deals with the Degrees-of-Freedom region of a Multiple-Input-Single-Output (MISO) Broadcast Channel (BC) with imperfect Channel State Information at the transmitter (CSIT). This topic falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the impact of CSIT on the DoF region, which is related to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a scheme for achieving the upper-bound for the general L-subband scenario in frequency domain BC, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
